headline: Cisco (CSCO): Reassessing Valuation After a 37% One-Year Share Price Climb
summary: Cisco Systems (CSCO) has been grinding higher this year, and the latest leg of that move has investors rechecking the story, especially with solid profit growth and a roughly 37% gain over the past year. See our latest analysis for Cisco Systems. That steady climb has left Cisco shares at about $78.25.
